Demonstration of indexed derived datatype

Indexed allows replication of an old datatype into a sequence of blocks, where
each block can contain a different number of copies and have a different
displacement. All block displacements are multiple of the old data type's
extent.

    int MPI_Type_indexed(int count, const int array_of_blocklengths[],
                         const int array_of_displacements[],
                         MPI_Datatype oldtype, MPI_Datatype *newtype)

       - count: Number of blocks — also number of entries in
         array_of_displacements and array_of_blocklengths (nonnegative
         integer).
       - array_of_blocklengths: Number of elements per block (array of
         nonnegative integers).
       - array_of_displacements: Displacement for each block, in multiples of
         oldtype extent
       - oldtype: Old datatype (handle).
       - newtype: New datatype (handle).
